main.project.obfuscation.tests

Interface ITest

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AllNamesTest, AverageLineTest, CommasPercentageTest, DefinedNamesTest, DigitsPercentageTest, EncodedCharTest, ExistenceOfReplaceTest, ExistenceOfSuspiciousSplitTest, GibberishTest, HexaDecimalVariableTest, LongStringsTest, StringEvaluationTest, UglyCodeTest, UppercasePercentageTest, WhitespacePercentageTest

    public interface ITest
    An interface for tests run by the JS obfuscation tester. Every test in this package implements ITest.

    • Method Detail

      • getTestWeight

        double getTestWeight()
        The getTestWeight function returns one of the following values, included in the 'WeightType' enum: VERY_LOW (1.0) LOW (2.0) MEDIUM (3.0) HIGH (4.0) VERY_HIGH (5.0)

      • isSuspicious

        boolean isSuspicious(java.lang.String javascriptPath,
                     java.lang.String javascriptCode)
        The implementation of the obfuscation test. isSuspicious is a boolean function that receives the JavaScript source code and test for suspiciousness according to the test criteria. If the function returns true (i.e test passed), the score returned from the getTestWeight function will be added to the total obfuscation score of the code.
        Parameters:
        javascriptPath - - path to JavaScript source file.
        javascriptCode - - the JavaScript source code.
        Returns:
        true if the code passes the test, false otherwise.
